</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37033D6FFCA507BFF5833709007521F" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD5605DFFCA507BFF58337097DF55B0" blockId="2.[158,801,1118,1974]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFF58337094505770" bold="true" box="[158,274,1119,1142]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The clade that includes 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFDE2337197EF5770" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Carvalho &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2005" box="[548,685,1118,1142]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Otothyropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFDE2337197EF5770" box="[548,685,1118,1142]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Otothyropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFD7B337196635770" authorityName="Myers" authorityYear="1927" box="[701,801,1118,1142]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Otothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFD7B337196635770" box="[701,801,1118,1142]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Otothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFF0A335194295790" authorityName="Britski &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="1984" box="[204,363,1150,1174]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudotothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFF0A335194295790" box="[204,363,1150,1174]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Pseudotothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the remaining genera of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFF5833B0942B57B0" authorityName="C.H.Eigenmann &amp; R.S.Eigenmann" authorityYear="1890" box="[158,361,1183,1206]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hypoptopomatinae">Hypoptopomatinae</taxonomicName>
by having an elongate posterior extension of the pterotic-supracleithrum which forms the dorsal margin of an enlarged lateral opening of the swimbladder capsule (
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFCC233F0965857F0" box="[772,794,1247,1270]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">vs</emphasis>
. quadrangular in shape and not extending posteriorly to form the dorsal margin of swimbladder capsule), and by having the supraoccipital forming the dorsal wall of the swimbladder capsule (
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFF1C327095B25670" box="[218,240,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">vs</emphasis>
. supraoccipital does not contribute to dorsal wall of swimbladder capsule) (derived states of characters 8 and 12 of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB1DACFFCA507BFF5832B0941556B0" author="Schaefer, S" box="[158,343,1439,1462]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" pagination="375 - 400" refId="ref6594" refString="Schaefer, S. A. 1998. Conflict and resolution: Impact of new taxa on phylogenetic studies of the neotropical cascudinhos (Siluriformes: Loricariidae). Pp. 375 - 400 In: L. R. Malabarba, R. E. Reis, R. P. Vari, C. A. S. Lucena &amp; Z. M. S. Lucena (Eds.). Phylogeny and Classification of Neotropical Fishes. Edipucrs, Porto Alegre. 603 p." type="book chapter" year="1998">Schaefer, 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFEA932B1974456B0" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Carvalho &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2005" box="[367,518,1438,1462]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Otothyropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFEA932B1974456B0" box="[367,518,1438,1462]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Otothyropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFF583291947F56D0" authorityName="Britski &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="1984" box="[158,317,1470,1494]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudotothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFF583291947F56D0" box="[158,317,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Pseudotothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFEB53291949556D0" authorityName="Myers" authorityYear="1927" box="[371,471,1470,1494]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Otothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFEB53291949556D0" box="[371,471,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Otothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having enlarged odontodes on the dorsal and ventral margins of the snout (
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFD6732F097F556F0" box="[673,695,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">vs</emphasis>
. enlarged odontodes only on the dorsal margin); by lacking conspicuous crests of enlarged odontodes on the tip of supraoccipital and pterotic-supracleithrum in adults (
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFDE8311097065550" box="[558,580,1599,1622]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">vs</emphasis>
. adults with well-developed crests), and by having the abdomen completely plated in adults (
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFECF3150945D5590" box="[265,287,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">vs</emphasis>
. adults with abdominal platelets reduced, sometimes restricted to lateral abdominal plate series).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD5605DFFCA507BFF0231909007521F" blockId="2.[158,801,1118,1974]" lastBlockId="2.[839,1481,194,281]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">
The following characters were considered autapomorphic in our reanalysis of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB1DACFFCA507BFEBD31F0977F55F0" author="Schaefer, S" box="[379,573,1759,1782]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" pagination="375 - 400" refId="ref6594" refString="Schaefer, S. A. 1998. Conflict and resolution: Impact of new taxa on phylogenetic studies of the neotropical cascudinhos (Siluriformes: Loricariidae). Pp. 375 - 400 In: L. R. Malabarba, R. E. Reis, R. P. Vari, C. A. S. Lucena &amp; Z. M. S. Lucena (Eds.). Phylogeny and Classification of Neotropical Fishes. Edipucrs, Porto Alegre. 603 p." type="book chapter" year="1998">Schaefer’s (1998)</bibRefCitation>
phylogenetic framework of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFEE531D094B75410" authorityName="C.H.Eigenmann &amp; R.S.Eigenmann" authorityYear="1890" box="[291,501,1791,1814]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hypoptopomatinae">Hypoptopomatinae</taxonomicName>
, and phylogenetically diagnoses the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFE473031974F5430" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Carvalho &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2005" box="[385,525,1822,1846]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Otothyropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFE473031974F5430" box="[385,525,1822,1846]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Otothyropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: presence of a single median rostral plate; presence of enlarged odontodes in both dorsal and ventral snout margins (derived conditions of characters, 34 and 39 of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB1DACFFCA507BFEBF3050976C5490" author="Schaefer, S" box="[377,558,1919,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" pagination="375 - 400" refId="ref6594" refString="Schaefer, S. A. 1998. Conflict and resolution: Impact of new taxa on phylogenetic studies of the neotropical cascudinhos (Siluriformes: Loricariidae). Pp. 375 - 400 In: L. R. Malabarba, R. E. Reis, R. P. Vari, C. A. S. Lucena &amp; Z. M. S. Lucena (Eds.). Phylogeny and Classification of Neotropical Fishes. Edipucrs, Porto Alegre. 603 p." type="book chapter" year="1998">Schaefer’s, 1998</bibRefCitation>
phylogeny); and presence of the ocular diverticulum (reversal of character 42 of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB1DACFFCA507BFC8137ED96BA53DF" author="Schaefer, S" box="[839,1016,194,217]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" pagination="375 - 400" refId="ref6594" refString="Schaefer, S. A. 1998. Conflict and resolution: Impact of new taxa on phylogenetic studies of the neotropical cascudinhos (Siluriformes: Loricariidae). Pp. 375 - 400 In: L. R. Malabarba, R. E. Reis, R. P. Vari, C. A. S. Lucena &amp; Z. M. S. Lucena (Eds.). Phylogeny and Classification of Neotropical Fishes. Edipucrs, Porto Alegre. 603 p." type="book chapter" year="1998">Schaefer’s, 1998</bibRefCitation>
phylogeny). None of these characters, however, are exclusive to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFB8437CE918F53FF" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Carvalho &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2005" box="[1090,1229,225,249]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Otothyropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFB8437CE918F53FF" box="[1090,1229,225,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Otothyropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being considered homoplasies according to the parsimony analysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37033D6FFCA507BFC81366D917752FF" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD5605DFFCA507BFC81366D917752FF" blockId="2.[839,1482,322,505]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFC81366D9686525F" bold="true" box="[839,964,322,345]" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Etymology.</emphasis>
The first part of the name is from Greek (
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFAA0366D90D0525F" box="[1382,1426,322,345]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">otos</emphasis>
= ear and 
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFCB1364E96F7527F" box="[887,949,353,377]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">thyris</emphasis>
= window) and is in reference to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFAA4364D96F4529F" authorityName="C.H.Eigenmann &amp; R.S.Eigenmann" authorityYear="1890" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hypoptopomatinae">Hypoptopomatinae</taxonomicName>
genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A1BDEFFCA507BFC3836AE9121529F" authorityName="Myers" authorityYear="1927" box="[1022,1123,385,409]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Otothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFC3836AE9121529F" box="[1022,1123,385,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">Otothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to which the new taxon is closely related. The second part is from the Greek (
<emphasis id="B91EBC4FFFCA507BFACB368D900652BF" box="[1293,1348,418,441]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="491">opsis</emphasis>
= relating to sight and appearance); hence, resembling a hypoptopomatine fish. Gender: feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
